---
import InfoLayout from '../layouts/InfoLayout.astro';
---

<InfoLayout
  title="Security · StudentLancers"
  description="How StudentLancers protects accounts, payments, and personal data."
  eyebrow="Security"
  heading="How we keep StudentLancers safe."
  lead="An honest summary of what we do, what we don't, and how to report a vulnerability."
>
  <h2>Account security</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Passwords are hashed with bcrypt (cost 12+).</li>
    <li>Optional two-factor authentication for company accounts.</li>
    <li>Session cookies are HttpOnly, Secure, and SameSite=Lax.</li>
    <li>Brute-force protection on the login and password-reset endpoints.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Payments</h2>
  <p>
    All payments flow through Stripe Connect. We are PCI-DSS compliant via
    Stripe's SAQ-A. Funds held in escrow sit in a separate, regulated
    account — they never co-mingle with operating funds.
  </p>

  <h2>Data</h2>
  <p>
    All data is encrypted in transit (TLS 1.3) and at rest (AES-256). Daily
    backups are stored in a separate region. We run annual third-party
    penetration tests.
  </p>

  <h2>Report a vulnerability</h2>
  <p>
    Found a bug or a security issue? Please email
    <a href="mailto:security@studentlancers.com">security@studentlancers.com</a>
    with a description and reproduction steps. We respond within one
    business day and credit researchers (with permission) in our public
    hall of fame.
  </p>
</InfoLayout>
